# E: drive only — keep C: clean

The owner works **exclusively** from `E:\Da-Music-Box-v4-SOURCE-COMPLETE`. **Never** write project files, caches, build output, or temp data to `C:`.

## Canonical locations (E:)

| Purpose | Path |
|---------|------|
| Source + git | `E:\Da-Music-Box-v4-SOURCE-COMPLETE\` |
| Vite cache | `E:\Da-Music-Box-v4-SOURCE-COMPLETE\.vite-cache\` |
| Production build | `E:\Da-Music-Box-v4-SOURCE-COMPLETE\dist\` |
| Bun install cache | `E:\Da-Music-Box-v4-SOURCE-COMPLETE\.cache\bun\` |
| Global Bun home (junction) | `E:\Da-Music-Box-v4-SOURCE-COMPLETE\.cache\bun-global\` |
| Cursor workspace data (junction) | `E:\Da-Music-Box-v4-SOURCE-COMPLETE\.cursor\workspace-data\` |
| Temp / scratch | `E:\Da-Music-Box-v4-SOURCE-COMPLETE\.cache\temp\` |
| User drum kits / downloads | `E:\Da-Music-Box-v4-SOURCE-COMPLETE\.cache\` |

`vite.config.ts` already pins `cacheDir` and `outDir` to E: when the drive is present.

## Forbidden for agents

- Hard-coded `C:\Users\...` paths in code, scripts, or docs for this project
- Defaulting caches to `%USERPROFILE%`, `%APPDATA%`, or `%TEMP%` on C: without redirecting to E:
- Creating duplicate project folders on C:
- Suggesting the user open or sync from a C: copy of the repo

## When adding tooling

- Put caches under `E:\Da-Music-Box-v4-SOURCE-COMPLETE\.cache\`
- Use relative paths from the repo root when possible
- Terminal env in `.vscode/settings.json` sets `TEMP`, `TMP`, and `BUN_INSTALL_CACHE_DIR` on E:
- Run `scripts/ensure-e-drive-paths.ps1` after a fresh machine setup to recreate junctions

## Note on Cursor IDE

Cursor itself installs under `%APPDATA%\Cursor` on C: (the editor binary). That is **system-level**, not project data. All **project-related** agent terminals, transcripts, and build caches must live on E: via the junctions above.
